WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.838 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.838 --> 00:00:12.275 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:12.275 --> 00:00:19.160 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:23.190 align:middle line:84%
>> In the beginning was
the logos, the Big Bang,

00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:26.120 align:middle line:90%
the primordial om.

00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:29.750 align:middle line:84%
Big Bang Theory says that the
physical universe spiraled out

00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:32.960 align:middle line:84%
of an unimaginably hot
and dense single point

00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:35.810 align:middle line:84%
called a singularity,
billions of times smaller

00:00:35.810 --> 00:00:38.990 align:middle line:90%
than the head of a pin.

00:00:38.990 --> 00:00:40.595 align:middle line:90%
It does not say why or how.

00:00:40.595 --> 00:00:43.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:45.810 align:middle line:84%
The more mysterious
something is,

00:00:45.810 --> 00:00:48.380 align:middle line:84%
the more we take for granted
that we understand it.

00:00:48.380 --> 00:01:00.520 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:02.700 align:middle line:84%
It was thought that
eventually gravity

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.730 align:middle line:84%
would either slow the
expansion or contract

00:01:05.730 --> 00:01:07.035 align:middle line:90%
the universe in a big crunch.

00:01:07.035 --> 00:01:09.550 align:middle line:90%


00:01:09.550 --> 00:01:12.490 align:middle line:84%
However, images from the
Hubble Space Telescope

00:01:12.490 --> 00:01:14.830 align:middle line:84%
show that the
universe's expansion

00:01:14.830 --> 00:01:18.010 align:middle line:84%
seems to be actually
accelerating,

00:01:18.010 --> 00:01:21.910 align:middle line:84%
expanding faster and faster as
it grows out of the Big Bang.

00:01:21.910 --> 00:01:24.830 align:middle line:90%


00:01:24.830 --> 00:01:27.710 align:middle line:84%
Somehow, there is more
mass in the universe

00:01:27.710 --> 00:01:30.410 align:middle line:90%
than physics predicted.

00:01:30.410 --> 00:01:33.860 align:middle line:84%
To account for the missing
mass, physicists now

00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:36.650 align:middle line:84%
say that the universe
consists of only 4%

00:01:36.650 --> 00:01:40.280 align:middle line:84%
atomic matter, or what we
consider normal matter.

00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:44.300 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:47.930 align:middle line:84%
23% of the universe
is dark matter.

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:51.920 align:middle line:84%
And 73% is dark energy,
what we previously

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:55.550 align:middle line:90%
thought of as empty space.

00:01:55.550 --> 00:01:57.830 align:middle line:10%
It is like an invisible
nervous system

00:01:57.830 --> 00:02:01.250 align:middle line:10%
that runs through the universe,
connecting all things.

00:02:01.250 --> 00:02:07.980 align:middle line:90%


00:02:07.980 --> 00:02:11.160 align:middle line:84%
The ancient vedic teachers
taught Nada Brahma.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:13.900 align:middle line:90%
The universe is vibration.

00:02:13.900 --> 00:02:15.630 align:middle line:84%
The vibratory field
is at the root

00:02:15.630 --> 00:02:19.190 align:middle line:84%
of all true spiritual experience
and scientific investigation.

00:02:19.190 --> 00:02:23.020 align:middle line:90%


00:02:23.020 --> 00:02:27.400 align:middle line:84%
It is the same field of energy
that saints, buddhas, yogis,

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:30.790 align:middle line:84%
mystics, priests,
shamans, and seers

00:02:30.790 --> 00:02:32.890 align:middle line:84%
have observed by looking
within themselves.

00:02:32.890 --> 00:02:37.580 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.580 --> 00:02:42.350 align:middle line:84%
It has been called
Akasha, the primordial om,

00:02:42.350 --> 00:02:47.210 align:middle line:84%
Indra's Net of Jewels,
the music of the spheres,

00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:49.625 align:middle line:84%
and a thousand other
names throughout history.

00:02:49.625 --> 00:03:00.860 align:middle line:90%


00:03:00.860 --> 00:03:07.970 align:middle line:84%
It is the common
root of all religions

00:03:07.970 --> 00:03:11.645 align:middle line:84%
and the link between our inner
worlds and our outer worlds.

00:03:11.645 --> 00:03:34.150 align:middle line:90%


00:03:34.150 --> 00:03:36.790 align:middle line:84%
In Mahayana Buddhism
in the third century,

00:03:36.790 --> 00:03:39.670 align:middle line:84%
they described a cosmology
not unlike the most advanced

00:03:39.670 --> 00:03:42.380 align:middle line:90%
physics of modern day.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:44.610 align:middle line:84%
Indra's Net of
Jewels is a metaphor

00:03:44.610 --> 00:03:48.030 align:middle line:84%
used to describe a much
older vedic teaching, which

00:03:48.030 --> 00:03:50.220 align:middle line:84%
illustrates the way the
fabric of the universe

00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:52.510 align:middle line:90%
is woven together.

00:03:52.510 --> 00:03:59.210 align:middle line:84%
Indra, the King of the
Gods, gave birth to the sun

00:03:59.210 --> 00:04:01.005 align:middle line:84%
and moves the winds
and the waters.

00:04:01.005 --> 00:04:04.180 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.180 --> 00:04:09.130 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a spiderweb that
extends into all dimensions.

00:04:09.130 --> 00:04:12.490 align:middle line:84%
The web is made up of
dew drops and every drop

00:04:12.490 --> 00:04:16.800 align:middle line:84%
contains the reflection of
all the other water drops.

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:19.180 align:middle line:84%
And in each reflected
dew drop, you

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:22.930 align:middle line:84%
will find the reflections
of all the other droplets,

00:04:22.930 --> 00:04:26.080 align:middle line:84%
the entire web in
that reflection,

00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:28.990 align:middle line:90%
and so on to infinity.

00:04:28.990 --> 00:04:32.690 align:middle line:84%
Indra's Web could be described
as a holographic universe,

00:04:32.690 --> 00:04:34.940 align:middle line:84%
where even the smallest
stream of light

00:04:34.940 --> 00:04:36.965 align:middle line:84%
contains the complete
pattern of the whole.

00:04:36.965 --> 00:04:42.520 align:middle line:90%


00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:45.860 align:middle line:84%
The Serbian-American
scientists, Nikola Tesla,

00:04:45.860 --> 00:04:47.720 align:middle line:84%
is sometimes referred
to as the man

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:50.540 align:middle line:90%
who invented the 20th century.

00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:52.460 align:middle line:84%
Tesla was responsible
for discovering

00:04:52.460 --> 00:04:56.000 align:middle line:84%
alternating current electricity
and many other creations that

00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:59.060 align:middle line:90%
are now part of everyday life.

00:04:59.060 --> 00:05:02.240 align:middle line:10%
Because of his interest in
the ancient vedic traditions,

00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:05.600 align:middle line:10%
Tesla was in a unique position
to understand science,

00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:07.505 align:middle line:10%
through both an eastern
and western model.

00:05:07.505 --> 00:05:10.040 align:middle line:90%


00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:13.130 align:middle line:84%
Like all great scientists,
Tesla look deeply

00:05:13.130 --> 00:05:15.590 align:middle line:84%
into the mysteries
of the outer world.

00:05:15.590 --> 00:05:19.430 align:middle line:84%
But he also looked
deeply within himself.

00:05:19.430 --> 00:05:23.540 align:middle line:84%
Like the ancient yogis,
Tesla used the term Akasha

00:05:23.540 --> 00:05:25.400 align:middle line:84%
to describe the
etheric field that

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:26.795 align:middle line:90%
extends throughout all things.

00:05:26.795 --> 00:05:31.580 align:middle line:90%


00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:34.310 align:middle line:84%
Tesla studied with
swami Vivekananda,

00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:38.660 align:middle line:84%
a yogi who brought the ancient
teachings of India to the West.

00:05:38.660 --> 00:05:42.650 align:middle line:84%
In the vedic teachings,
Akasha is space itself,

00:05:42.650 --> 00:05:45.180 align:middle line:84%
the space that the
other elements fill,

00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:49.040 align:middle line:84%
which exist simultaneously
with vibration.

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:51.620 align:middle line:90%
The two are inseparable.

00:05:51.620 --> 00:05:54.410 align:middle line:90%
Akasha is yin to Prana's yang.

00:05:54.410 --> 00:06:05.270 align:middle line:90%


00:06:05.270 --> 00:06:07.760 align:middle line:84%
A modern concept that can
help us to conceptualize

00:06:07.760 --> 00:06:10.070 align:middle line:84%
Akasha, or the
primary substance,

00:06:10.070 --> 00:06:11.330 align:middle line:90%
is the idea of fractals.

00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:15.880 align:middle line:90%


00:06:15.880 --> 00:06:20.230 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't until the 1980s
that advances in computers

00:06:20.230 --> 00:06:22.390 align:middle line:84%
allowed us to actually
visualize and reproduce,

00:06:22.390 --> 00:06:26.350 align:middle line:84%
mathematically, the
patterns in nature.

00:06:26.350 --> 00:06:29.110 align:middle line:10%
The term fractal
was coined in 1980

00:06:29.110 --> 00:06:31.660 align:middle line:10%
by mathematician
Manuel Mandelbrot, who

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:34.000 align:middle line:10%
studied certain simple
mathematical equations

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.160 align:middle line:10%
that, when they are
repeated, produce

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:39.430 align:middle line:10%
an unending array of changing
mathematical or geometrical

00:06:39.430 --> 00:06:42.460 align:middle line:10%
forms within a
limited framework.

00:06:42.460 --> 00:06:46.278 align:middle line:84%
They are limited, but at
the same time, infinite.

00:06:46.278 --> 00:06:49.210 align:middle line:90%


00:06:49.210 --> 00:06:51.570 align:middle line:84%
A fractal is a rough
geometric shape

00:06:51.570 --> 00:06:54.540 align:middle line:84%
that can be split into
parts, each of which

00:06:54.540 --> 00:06:56.850 align:middle line:84%
is at least approximately
a reduced size

00:06:56.850 --> 00:06:59.940 align:middle line:84%
copy of the whole
pattern, a property

00:06:59.940 --> 00:07:01.320 align:middle line:90%
called self-similarity.

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:05.100 align:middle line:90%


00:07:05.100 --> 00:07:08.430 align:middle line:84%
Mandelbrot's fractals have being
called the Thumbprint of God.

00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:11.580 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:22.690 align:middle line:90%


00:07:22.690 --> 00:07:26.690 align:middle line:84%
You are seeing artwork
generated by nature itself.

00:07:26.690 --> 00:07:29.870 align:middle line:84%
If you turn the Mandelbrot
figure a certain way,

00:07:29.870 --> 00:07:33.560 align:middle line:84%
it looks sort of like a
Hindu deity or Buddha.

00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:35.900 align:middle line:10%
This figure is being
termed a Buddhabrot figure.

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:57.260 align:middle line:90%


00:07:57.260 --> 00:08:00.950 align:middle line:10%
If you look at some forms of
ancient art and architecture,

00:08:00.950 --> 00:08:02.510 align:middle line:10%
you will see that
humans have long

00:08:02.510 --> 00:08:05.810 align:middle line:10%
associated beauty and the
sacred with fractal patterns.

00:08:05.810 --> 00:08:17.820 align:middle line:90%


00:08:17.820 --> 00:08:20.430 align:middle line:84%
Infinitely complex,
yet every part

00:08:20.430 --> 00:08:23.970 align:middle line:84%
contains the seed to
recreate the whole.

00:08:23.970 --> 00:08:25.800 align:middle line:84%
Fractals have changed
mathematicians

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:29.550 align:middle line:84%
views of the universe
and how it operates.

00:08:29.550 --> 00:08:32.340 align:middle line:84%
With each new level
of magnification,

00:08:32.340 --> 00:08:35.309 align:middle line:84%
there are differences
from the original.

00:08:35.309 --> 00:08:37.350 align:middle line:84%
Constant change
and transformation

00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:40.620 align:middle line:84%
occurs as we traverse from
one level of fractal detail

00:08:40.620 --> 00:08:42.450 align:middle line:90%
to another.

00:08:42.450 --> 00:08:46.040 align:middle line:84%
This transformation
is the cosmic spiral,

00:08:46.040 --> 00:08:48.905 align:middle line:84%
the embedded intelligence
of the matrix of time space.

00:08:48.905 --> 00:09:14.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.130 --> 00:09:19.770 align:middle line:84%
Fractals are inherently chaotic,
full of noise and order.

00:09:19.770 --> 00:09:22.620 align:middle line:84%
When our minds recognize
or define a pattern,

00:09:22.620 --> 00:09:26.670 align:middle line:84%
we focus on it, as
if it is a thing.

00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:29.730 align:middle line:84%
We try to find the patterns
we see as beautiful.

00:09:29.730 --> 00:09:32.670 align:middle line:84%
But in order to hold the
pattern in our minds,

00:09:32.670 --> 00:09:34.470 align:middle line:84%
we must push away the
rest of the fractal.

00:09:34.470 --> 00:09:53.110 align:middle line:90%


00:09:53.110 --> 00:09:55.863 align:middle line:10%
To comprehend a
fractal with a census

00:09:55.863 --> 00:09:56.905 align:middle line:10%
is to limit its movement.

00:09:56.905 --> 00:10:01.010 align:middle line:90%


00:10:01.010 --> 00:10:04.360 align:middle line:10%
All energy and the universe
is neutral, timeless,

00:10:04.360 --> 00:10:05.360 align:middle line:10%
dimensionless.

00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:10.080 align:middle line:90%


00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:13.530 align:middle line:84%
Our own creativity and capacity
for pattern recognition

00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:17.460 align:middle line:84%
is the link between the
microcosm and macrocosm,

00:10:17.460 --> 00:10:21.265 align:middle line:84%
the timeless world of waves,
and the solid world of things.

00:10:21.265 --> 00:10:26.340 align:middle line:90%


00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:28.350 align:middle line:84%
Observation is an
act of creation

00:10:28.350 --> 00:10:31.440 align:middle line:84%
through limitations
inherent in thinking.

00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:34.650 align:middle line:84%
We are creating the illusion
of solidity, of things

00:10:34.650 --> 00:10:37.640 align:middle line:90%
by labeling, by naming.

00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:41.220 align:middle line:84%
The philosopher Kierkegaard
said, "If you name me,

00:10:41.220 --> 00:10:43.080 align:middle line:90%
you negate me.

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:45.810 align:middle line:84%
By giving me a
name, a label, you

00:10:45.810 --> 00:10:49.820 align:middle line:84%
negate all of the other
things I could possibly be.

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:52.490 align:middle line:84%
You lock the particle
into being a thing

00:10:52.490 --> 00:10:55.550 align:middle line:90%
by pinning it down, naming it.

00:10:55.550 --> 00:10:58.130 align:middle line:10%
But at the same time,
you are creating it,

00:10:58.130 --> 00:10:59.285 align:middle line:10%
defining it to exist."

00:10:59.285 --> 00:11:02.780 align:middle line:90%


00:11:02.780 --> 00:11:06.260 align:middle line:84%
Creativity is our
highest nature.

00:11:06.260 --> 00:11:08.720 align:middle line:84%
With the creation
of things comes

00:11:08.720 --> 00:11:12.230 align:middle line:84%
time, which is what creates
the illusion of solidity.

00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:20.510 align:middle line:90%


00:11:20.510 --> 00:11:22.760 align:middle line:84%
Einstein was the first
scientist to realize

00:11:22.760 --> 00:11:26.460 align:middle line:84%
that what we think of as
empty space is not nothing.

00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:28.390 align:middle line:90%
It has properties.

00:11:28.390 --> 00:11:30.260 align:middle line:84%
And intrinsic to
the nature of space

00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:32.330 align:middle line:84%
is nearly unfathomable
amounts of energy.

00:11:32.330 --> 00:11:35.060 align:middle line:90%


00:11:35.060 --> 00:11:37.100 align:middle line:84%
The renowned physicist
Richard Feynman

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:39.800 align:middle line:84%
once said, "There
is enough energy

00:11:39.800 --> 00:11:42.830 align:middle line:84%
in a single cubic
meter of space to boil

00:11:42.830 --> 00:11:44.195 align:middle line:90%
all the oceans in the world."

00:11:44.195 --> 00:11:48.080 align:middle line:90%


00:11:48.080 --> 00:11:50.870 align:middle line:84%
Advanced meditators know
that in the stillness

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:51.980 align:middle line:90%
lies the greatest power.

00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:56.180 align:middle line:90%


00:11:56.180 --> 00:11:59.780 align:middle line:10%
The Buddha had yet another term
for the primary substance, what

00:11:59.780 --> 00:12:03.500 align:middle line:10%
he termed kalapas, which
are like tiny particles

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:07.070 align:middle line:10%
or wavelets that are
rising and passing away

00:12:07.070 --> 00:12:08.715 align:middle line:10%
trillions of times per second.

00:12:08.715 --> 00:12:15.290 align:middle line:90%


00:12:15.290 --> 00:12:18.440 align:middle line:84%
Reality is, in this
sense, like a series

00:12:18.440 --> 00:12:21.950 align:middle line:84%
of frames in a
holographic film camera,

00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:27.260 align:middle line:84%
moving quickly, so as to create
the illusion of continuity.

00:12:27.260 --> 00:12:30.140 align:middle line:84%
When consciousness
becomes perfectly still,

00:12:30.140 --> 00:12:32.780 align:middle line:84%
the illusion is
understood, because it

00:12:32.780 --> 00:12:35.570 align:middle line:84%
is consciousness itself
that drives the illusion.

00:12:35.570 --> 00:13:18.050 align:middle line:90%


00:13:18.050 --> 00:13:20.510 align:middle line:84%
In the ancient
traditions of the east,

00:13:20.510 --> 00:13:22.640 align:middle line:84%
it has been understood
for thousands of years

00:13:22.640 --> 00:13:31.950 align:middle line:84%
that all is vibration, Nada
Brahma, the universe's sound.

00:13:31.950 --> 00:13:35.210 align:middle line:84%
The word Nada means
sound or vibration.

00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:38.330 align:middle line:90%
And Brahma is the name for God.

00:13:38.330 --> 00:13:43.550 align:middle line:84%
Brahma simultaneously is the
universe and is the creator.

00:13:43.550 --> 00:13:45.890 align:middle line:84%
The artist and the
art are inseparable.

00:13:45.890 --> 00:13:48.950 align:middle line:90%


00:13:48.950 --> 00:13:52.160 align:middle line:84%
In the Upanishads, one of
the oldest human records

00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:55.490 align:middle line:84%
from ancient India,
it is said Brahma

00:13:55.490 --> 00:14:00.410 align:middle line:84%
the creator, sitting on
a lotus, opens his eyes

00:14:00.410 --> 00:14:01.745 align:middle line:90%
and a world comes into being.

00:14:01.745 --> 00:14:05.660 align:middle line:90%


00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:09.185 align:middle line:84%
Brahma closes his eyes and
a world goes out of being.

00:14:09.185 --> 00:14:13.700 align:middle line:90%


00:14:13.700 --> 00:14:15.948 align:middle line:84%
Ancient mystics,
yogis, and seers

00:14:15.948 --> 00:14:17.990 align:middle line:84%
have maintained that there
is a field at the root

00:14:17.990 --> 00:14:22.280 align:middle line:84%
level of consciousness,
the Akashic field,

00:14:22.280 --> 00:14:25.940 align:middle line:84%
or the Akashic records,
where all information,

00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:29.390 align:middle line:84%
all experience, past,
present, and future,

00:14:29.390 --> 00:14:32.280 align:middle line:90%
exists now and always.

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:36.080 align:middle line:84%
It is this field or matrix
from which all things arise,

00:14:36.080 --> 00:14:41.305 align:middle line:84%
from subatomic particles to
galaxies, stars, planets,

00:14:41.305 --> 00:14:42.105 align:middle line:90%
and all life.

00:14:42.105 --> 00:14:51.070 align:middle line:90%


00:14:51.070 --> 00:14:53.970 align:middle line:84%
You never see anything
in its totality,

00:14:53.970 --> 00:14:58.040 align:middle line:84%
because it is made up of
layer upon layer of vibration

00:14:58.040 --> 00:15:01.595 align:middle line:84%
and it is constantly changing,
exchanging information

00:15:01.595 --> 00:15:02.395 align:middle line:90%
with Akasha.

00:15:02.395 --> 00:15:05.010 align:middle line:90%


00:15:05.010 --> 00:15:11.955 align:middle line:84%
A tree is drinking in the sun,
the air, the rain, the earth.

00:15:11.955 --> 00:15:16.800 align:middle line:90%


00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:18.840 align:middle line:84%
A world of energy
moves in and out

